description: Either from Shillelagh, County Wicklow, in Ireland (from Irish Síol (“descendants”) + Éalaigh (a name)), because the forest near it provided the wood from which such clubs were made; or from sail (“cudgel”) + éille (“thong”).

entries.meaning: (Ireland) A wooden (traditionally blackthorn (sloe) wood) club ending with a large knob.
Any cudgel, whether or not of Irish origin.
